Use Case Name: Display Order Type Indicator
 Primary Actor: Restaurant Staff
stakeholders & Interests:
•	Restaurant Staff: Need to quickly identify order types to ensure proper handling and routing.
•	Customers: Expect accurate preparation and correct fulfillment of their orders.
•	Management: Wants efficient operations with minimal order-type mix-ups.
•	System Administrator: Requires clear and consistent indicator setup for all order types.
Preconditions:
•	Order exists in the system with its order type (to-go, pick-up, or delivery) defined.
•	The order is marked as completed.
Success Conditions:
•	Each completed order displays a visible indicator showing its type.
•	Staff can distinguish all completed orders at a glance with no ambiguity.
•	The system shows consistent and accurate indicators for every completed order.
Frequency of Occurrence:
•	Occurs continuously throughout each business day as orders are completed.

Main Success Scenario:
User Action 	                            System Actions
1. Staff member selects “Complete Order”
                                            2. Record order as completed
                                            3. Retrieve the order type
                                            4. Determines and assigns the correct visual indicator for the order type.
                                            5. Display Completed orders list with associated visual indicators

6. Staff views the “Completed Orders” list to verify the order’s type.

Use Case Name: Saving system data
Primary Actor: System Manager
Stakeholder & Interests:
The Restaurant – Wants to have a reliable system that will store their information during a crash
The customer – They want their order to be correct
Preconditions:
-	There must already be data such as restaurants/orders
Success Conditions: System adds data and saves every action then loads data successfully.
Frequency Occurrence: Multiple times a day
Main Success Scenario:
User Action	            System Actions
1.Uses an action
 	                    2. System calls for data saving function
3. Manager ends system
 	                    4. System Exits
5. Manager reopen system
 	                    6. System loads the saved data


Use Case Name: Exporting all orders from a Restaurant
Primary Actor: System Manager
Stakeholder & Interests:
The restaurant – Want to know the order data for further analysis
Preconditions:
-	Must have at least 1 order
Success Conditions: Export all the orders into a single file in the directory of the Restaurant
Main Success Scenario:
User Action	                System Actions
1. Selects Export Orders.
                            2. System exports all orders to file.

